These are Puzzles for 2x2 Level 8

.:: Puzzle 2x2-Level-8-1::.
There 2 different types of food: apricot, radish
The people use 2 different means of transport: quad-bike, tram
1. the person driving the quad-bike is on the right of the person driving the tram##1
2. the person eating apricot is not to the right of the person driving the tram##8

.:: Answer ::.
|             |    1    |    2     |
| Food        | apricot   | radish   |
| Transport   | tram | quad-bike |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 2x2-Level-8-2::.
There are 2 different favourite beverages: tea, lemonade
The people prefer 2 different types of sport: sailing, basketball
1. the person who's sport is sailing is not to the left of the person drinking lemonade##8
2. the person who's sport is sailing is somewhere to the right of the person drinking lemonade##5

.:: Answer ::.
|            |    1     |    2    |
| Beverage   | lemonade | tea   |
| Sport      | basketball | sailing |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 2x2-Level-8-3::.
There 2 different types of food: corn, strawberry
The people prefer 2 different music-genres: blues, metal
1. the person eating corn is not to the left of the fan of metal##8
2. the person eating strawberry is on the left of the fan of metal##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |   1   |    2    |
| Food          | strawberry | corn |
| Music-Genre   | blues   | metal     |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 2x2-Level-8-4::.
